<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-10-24T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-10-24T19:00:00-05:00" n="324" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d324">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/14175a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul General at Hong Kong</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Southard</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-24T19:00:00-05:00">October 24, 1938—7
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>4. The Department desires to receive by telegraph from each of the
                                three offices to which this telegram is addressed a confidential
                                comprehensive summary report of the factors believed to be
                                responsible for the rapidity of the Japanese invasion of South China
                                and the comparative ease with which the Japanese have occupied
                                Canton.</p>
                            <p>Repeated to Canton and Chungking.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>